&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=3D&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=\r\n=3D&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;&quot;&gt;It is my be=\r\nlief that you\nhave probably incorrectly understood some of Narasimha&#39;s poin=\r\nts. He is not\nsaying that a grossly mispronounced mantra will give you spec=\r\nific results, BUT,\nif the fear of the 64 things that bind a mantra stops an=\r\n individual from even\ntrying to do japa, THAT is an even more serious probl=\r\nem. Therefore, his advise\nwas to start doing sadhana in whatever way possib=\r\nle without getting bogged down\nby technicalities too much.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span=\r\n&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p class=3D&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=3D&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-size: 12pt; fo=\r\nnt-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;&quot;&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n\n&lt;p c=\r\nlass=3D&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=3D&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-size: 12pt; font-famil=\r\ny: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;&quot;&gt;Thanks for your kind\nreview. But I think y=\r\nou didn=E2=80=99t read me as a whole. When I first read\nNarsinha=E2=80=99s&lt;=\r\nspan style=3D&quot;&quot;&gt;&nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;post I just took a printout\n,again read it as=\r\n a whole in my pastime and then started some thinking as what\nhe wrote was =\r\nnot complementary to scripture references on such imp subtle topic.\nThis wh=\r\nole dissection consists of mainly two points; whether yajamana gets\ndesired=\r\n results through priest=E2=80=99s shakti or by devata shakti and focus of m=\r\nind\nw.r.t. rituals,&lt;span style=3D&quot;&quot;&gt;&nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;arrangement of\nmantraword=\r\ns, power of words, etc. including generic mantra subtopic. From my\nside thi=\r\ns is due to mixing of religion and spirituality. Religion as a whole is\nfor=\r\n all four purusharthas i.e. dharma, artha, &lt;st1:place w:st=3D&quot;on&quot;&gt;kama&lt;/st1=\r\n:place&gt;\nand m